{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"undo-tabby-guy","description":"The plan-review gate's deterministic check **P2 (\"resolution\") abstains `no_repo_root`** on the normal `attested` CLI/library path, so the LLM plan-completeness findings cannot be code-grounded and land as `indeterminate / reason: no-verification` (validity 0, severity none) instead of being verified into advisory or dropped. The verdict still computes (PASS when 0 blocking), but the review is running effectively blind to the code.\n\n## Root cause (proven via joe-debug, runtime evidence)\nThere is no single authoritative resolver for the gate's *code read-root*; it is threaded ad-hoc across five hops (`review_plan → produce_plan_review_verdict → run_workflow → StepContext → workflow op → assemble_context`). At the `produce_plan_review_verdict` hop the already-resolved `ctx.repo_root` (= `cfg.repo_path` = the attested origin/main snapshot) was **discarded** — `repo_root=None` was passed into `run_workflow`. The det-floor op `plan_review_precheck` then called `assemble_context(tid, repo_root=None)` with no `cfg`, so `PlanContext.repo_root` was `None` and `det_floor.p2_resolution` abstained `no_repo_root` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py:227`). The degraded/step-budget-fail path ran the det floor on the *original* ctx (which had `repo_root`), which is why a step-budget-failed run showed P2 **pass** — the inconsistency fingerprint.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. From the repo venv: `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS=50 rebar review-plan <task-id> -o json`.\n2. Inspect `coverage.det.P2` → before the fix: `{\"status\": \"abstain\", \"ran\": false, \"reason\": \"no_repo_root\"}`.\n3. Observe the LLM findings come back as `indeterminate` with `reason: \"no-verification\"`.\n\n- **Expected:** in a gate run an attested snapshot is active (origin/main HEAD by default), so P2 runs against it (`ran: true`) and findings are code-grounded (verified → advisory, or refuted → dropped).\n- **Actual:** P2 abstains `no_repo_root`; findings are parked as `no-verification` indeterminate.\n\n## Fix (class-level, not just the immediate bug)\nCentralize code-read-root resolution into a single resolver and use it at the seams, so the \"None → silent degrade\" class is eliminated and the snapshot defaults to origin/main HEAD cleanly when nothing is specified:\n- `rebar.llm.config.resolve_code_root(repo_root=None, *, cfg_repo_path=None, allow_checkout_fallback=True)` — cascade: explicit `repo_root` > `cfg.repo_path` > active attested snapshot (`current_code_root`, origin/main HEAD by default) > live checkout. Default never returns None; `allow_checkout_fallback=False` yields snapshot-or-None for lightweight builders that must not force a checkout root (which would induce cache writes).\n- `orchestrator.assemble_context` resolves the `PlanContext.repo_root` field via the resolver (snapshot-or-None) — so EVERY workflow det-floor/grounding op picks up the active snapshot.\n- `gate_dispatch.produce_plan_review_verdict` threads the resolved root into `run_workflow` and the agentic `RunnerAgentStep` (so the det floor, grounding, and agentic verifier all read the pinned code).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A single `resolve_code_root` resolver exists with the documented cascade and never returns None by default (unit test covers all four cascade levels + the `allow_checkout_fallback=False` None branch).\n- [ ] `assemble_context` no longer yields `PlanContext.repo_root=None` when an attested snapshot is active; off-gate callers (no snapshot, no cfg) keep `None` (no checkout-write regression).\n- [ ] `produce_plan_review_verdict` threads the resolved snapshot into `run_workflow` and `RunnerAgentStep` (regression test asserts both, with a mutation check).\n- [ ] A real `rebar review-plan` in attested mode reports `coverage.det.P2.ran == true` (not `no_repo_root`) and findings are grounded (no `no-verification` indeterminate set purely from a missing repo root).\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make typecheck` clean; the plan_review/workflow/config unit suites pass with no repo-root leak-guard failures.","id":"9064-46cf-75dd-4f85","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Plan-review gate: P2 abstains no_repo_root on attested path; centralize code-root resolution"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782621309016462001,"uuid":"7e2e43bb-1b92-4599-9d98-eb6d86a73860"}